This product includes security testing methodology and framework references derived
from the following open standards and community resources. The frameworks themselves
are owned by their respective organizations; this skill consolidates testing guidance
informed by their publicly available documentation.

OWASP Foundation (https://owasp.org/)
  - OWASP Top 10, ASVS, SAMM, WSTG, MASVS, API Security Top 10, Mobile Top 10,
    LLM Top 10, Cloud-Native Top 10, Kubernetes Top 10
  - Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0

MITRE Corporation (https://www.mitre.org/)
  - ATT&CK, D3FEND, CALDERA, CWE, CAPEC
  - Licensed per MITRE terms for public use

NIST (https://www.nist.gov/)
  - Cybersecurity Framework 2.0, SP 800-53, SP 800-61, Risk Management Framework
  - U.S. Government work, public domain

ISO/IEC
  - ISO 27001, 27002, 27701, 27017, 27018, 27005, 27035 referenced by name only

CIS (https://www.cisecurity.org/)
  - CIS Controls, CIS Benchmarks referenced for context

Cloud Security Alliance (https://cloudsecurityalliance.org/)
  - Cloud Controls Matrix, CAIQ, STAR framework

Red Canary (https://redcanary.com/)
  - Atomic Red Team testing library referenced

ISECOM (https://www.isecom.org/)
  - OSSTMM with RAV methodology

